## MCP Servers

This project includes MCP server configurations in `.warp/mcp.json`. Import this file
via Warp's MCP settings (`Settings > AI > Manage MCP servers > + Add`).

The following server categories are enabled:

{% if ai_tools_mcp_thinking | default(true) %}- **Thinking**: Sequential, structured, cascade reasoning{% endif %}
{% if ai_tools_mcp_web | default(true) %}- **Web**: Fetch, Playwright browser automation{% endif %}
{% if ai_tools_mcp_documents | default(true) %}- **Documents**: Docling (PDF/DOCX), Repomix{% endif %}
{% if ai_tools_mcp_utilities | default(true) %}- **Utilities**: Memory persistence{% endif %}
{% if ai_tools_mcp_search | default(false) %}- **Search**: Brave, Tavily (requires API keys in env){% endif %}
{% if mcp_module == 'enabled' %}- **Project**: `{{ project_slug }}` MCP server{% endif %}

## Warp-Specific Notes

- Use `uv run python ...` instead of `python` directly
- Check for running dev servers before launching new ones
- Use playwright MCP tools to verify frontend changes
